<component type="desktop-application">
  <id>net.emulicious.Emulicious</id>
  <name>Emulicious</name>
  <summary>Multi-system emulator</summary>
  <metadata_license>CC0-1.0</metadata_license>
  <project_license>LicenseRef-Emulicious</project_license>
  <developer id="net.emulicious">
    <name translate="no">Michael Stegmaier (Calindro)</name>
  </developer>
  <description>
    <p>
      **Emulicious** is a Game Boy, Game Boy Color, Master System, Game Gear and MSX Emulator.
    </p>
    <p>
      Even though **Emulicious** aims for precision and accurate emulation it still provides some additional features and tools:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Automatic Updates</li>
      <li>Adjustable Turbo</li>
      <li>Adjustable Throttle</li>
      <li>IPS Patching</li>
      <li>Save states</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      **Emulicious** provides many features that can be useful for ROM hacking and Homebrew development:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Debugger</li>
      <li>Profiler</li>
      <li>Tracer</li>
      <li>Memory Editor</li>
      <li>Palette Viewer</li>
      <li>Tile Viewer</li>
      <li>Tilemap Viewer</li>
      <li>Sprite Viewer</li>
      <li>Sound Viewer</li>
      <li>etc...</li>
    </ul>
    <p>**To enable VSCode debugging support follow the guide at https://github.com/aquacash5/emulicious-flatpak**</p>
  </description>
